programme.title: Card Sharks
programme.desc: This show from legendary Mark Goodson-Bill Todman Productions features two contestants trying to predict answers to survey questions for the opportunity to play a game with oversized playing cards for a chance to win cash. One contestant guesses how many people (out of 100) gave a certain answer to a question and the other contestant then guesses if the number is higher or lower than the opponent's guess. The winning contestant then faces a row of cards and must determine if each succeeding card is higher or lower than the one that precedes it. The contestant who wins two out of three games wins the match and plays the bonus round, called Money Cards. The Money Cards round is similar to the card game in the main game but with three levels of cards instead of one row. The contestant is given $200 at the beginning of Money Cards and wagers any or all of that money when guessing if the cards will be higher or lower than the previous one. A perfect round could earn the contestant $28,800.

But greedy contractor Sam Brady (Robert Livingston) enjoys a monopoly on the transportation of crushed rock, which is being used to build a local dam. U.S. Marshal Gene Autry (Gene Autry), however, discovers that Brady has used this method before, and his dams always burst shortly after construction, flooding entire towns. Despite Brady's power, Autry campaigns to have the new dam made of cement.

programme.title: Saddle Pals
programme.desc: Rancher Gene (Gene Autry) pays a visit to Brooks (Sterling Holloway), the head of the company that owns his land. Brooks is tired of his corporate duties and so aggravated by his work that he impulsively offers Gene control of the company. Gene accepts, despite the corporation's debts, but after a meeting with two corrupt board members, he's told he must raise $50,000 to keep the business alive. Meanwhile, the board members, who want the company for themselves, plot to get Gene in legal trouble.

programme.title: Goldtown Ghost Riders
programme.desc: Gene Autry (Gene Autry) is the circuit judge for a small town when recently released convict Ed Wheeler (Kirk Riley) tries to kill a man named Jim Granby (Carleton Young). When Gene takes Ed into custody and prepares to put him on trial for the attempted murder of Granby, Ed tells a story about his past that may save him. Describing his early gold scavenging days, Ed claims that he has already completed a sentence for the very same crime: killing Jim Granby.

programme.title: The Last of the Pony Riders
programme.desc: Gene Autry (Gene Autry) works for the Pony Express, which is becoming obsolete due to the rapid onset of modernization, including the telegraph. When Gene brings an innovative idea to his employer, Tom (John Downey), he's fired. Meanwhile, Clyde Vesey (Howard Wright) tries to steal Tom's business by pressuring him to repay a loan and obstructing Pony Express riders. Despite having been fired, Gene follows Clyde's henchmen and tries to stand up for Tom and his family.

programme.title: On Top of Old Smoky
programme.desc: Singing cowboy Gene Autry (Gene Autry) and his sidekick, Smiley (Smiley Burnette), are performing with the Cass County Boys when they're mistaken for Texas Rangers. Despite their protests, they're soon involved in a dispute between tol road owner Jen Larrabee (Gail Davis) and Doc Judson (Grandon Rhodes) over Larrabee's property, which contains mineral deposits. Judson has been trying to coerce Larrabee into selling, but Gene and Smiley are determined to protect her land.

programme.title: Pack Train
programme.desc: Singing cowboy Gene Autry (Gene Autry) and his good pal Dan Coleman (Tom London) agree to help the pioneer residents of Sunshine Valley get much-needed food and medical supplies after the owners of a local store, Ross McLain (Kenne Duncan) and Lola Riker (Sheila Ryan), rip them off. However, getting the goods to the pioneers is a dangerous job. On the way to the valley, Autry -- with his trusty horse, Champion -- and Coleman are attacked by bandits led by the dastardly McLain.

programme.title: White of the Eye

As Paul's behavior turns violent, she begins to suspect her husband's guilt. To help, the Library recruits Eve, a counterterrorism agent responsible for organizational security; Jacob, who has encyclopedic knowledge of art, architecture and history; Cassandra, who links auditory/sensory hallucinations to memory; and Ezekiel, a skilled thief and master technician. Overseeing them is Jenkins, the reclusive caretaker of the Library's sleepy little annex in Oregon. Noah Wyle executive produces and recurs as Flynn, the role he played in the movie series.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, theyll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider whos never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, QUEENS &amp; COWBOYS weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.
